Summary

Gate-A patch (Prisma enums, BigInt, composite indexes, cookie note) validated and non-destructive. Session groundwork is acceptable with server-only migration path guarded by a feature flag.

Conditions (Carried into Phase-2 / Gate-B)
	1.	CSRF Enforcement: Require anti-CSRF token for all state-changing endpoints (POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE).
	2.	OAuth PKCE (S256): Enforce PKCE on authorization code flow.
	3.	Token Encryption at Rest: Implement AES-GCM app-level encryption for sessions.accessToken and sessions.refreshToken with key rotation (env/KMS). Prefer Prisma middleware for transparent encrypt/decrypt.
	4.	Logging Redaction: Ensure secrets/tokens are redacted (last-4 policy) in all logs.
	5.	Time & TZ Discipline: Normalize timestamps to UTC in DB and ISO-8601 Z on API responses.

